<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Skill Mods:</STRONG> 6 (just giving its worth, since I can't think of what mod types are best suited)<BR><STRONG>Click Effects:</STRONG> Epic click is nice, but things to help a bard stay alive are a plus.<BR><STRONG>Proc Effects:</STRONG> Likewise, lifetaps/heals/heal over times/runes are all good to keep a bard from dying, due to lack of other forms of direct healing. Also, proc rate mods on weapons are a very handy thing.<BR><STRONG>Worn Effects:</STRONG> I personally don't put much value in worn effects like Faerune anymore, due to AA's to replace the entire effect. I would personally like to see something like a +agro mod so a strong bard can help tank something as needed, but it's a bit of a stretch.<BR><STRONG>Focus Effects:</STRONG> This doesn't apply in most cases, and instrument mod caps probably aren't a part of your field, so I'm going to leave this one without a real answer.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As a note, I didn't give anything a 10 because so many of the listed statistics have caps, so a balance with fairly great amounts of everything, but not excessive, still adds up quickly.</DIV><p>Message Edited by Haliken-Innoruuk on <span class=date_text>07-06-2006</span> <span class=time_text>01:02 PM</span>
				
